The Sales Analytics Dashboard provides a comprehensive view of business performance across revenue,
profitability, products, customers, and regions. Analysis of the dashboard indicates that revenue growth was primarily 
driven by strong sales performance in high-performing regions, while certain regions showed declining revenue trends and lower profit margins.
Gross profit and margin analysis revealed that although some product categories generated high sales volumes, they contributed lower profitability 
due to higher operational or product costs. Customer analysis identified that premium and repeat customers contributed a significant share of total revenue,
highlighting the importance of customer retention strategies. The dashboard also helped identify low-margin products that negatively impacted overall profitability, 
enabling targeted business decisions around pricing, promotions, or product optimization. Time intelligence analysis showed month-over-month revenue fluctuations and
provided visibility into seasonal trends, supporting better forecasting and strategic planning. Through drill-through analysis and interactive reporting, stakeholders can 
move from high-level executive summaries to detailed customer and product-level insights, allowing faster identification of business risks, growth opportunities, and operational improvements.
